al information and indices. Dr Christine Raueris a Senior Lecturer in the School of English and the Institute of Mediaeval Studies at the University of St Andrews, Scotland.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristian martyrsvEarly works to 1800. 0aChristian martyrsxEarly works to 1800. 4aHistory of Religion. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aAnglo-Saxon.  aBiblical Events.  aCosmology.  aEnglish studies.  aMartyrology.  aMediaeval Studies.  aMiracle Stories.  aOld English.  aReference.  aSaints.  aearly modern history.  aliterature.  amauscript.  amedieval history.  amedieval literature.  amiddle ages.  areligion and classics.  asaints.  asociology.  atranslation.1 aRauer, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRauer, Christine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178204157340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782041573423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782041573/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles